definition: to arrange/to line up/file/series/(in data tables) column/(Tw) row

pinyin: pu3 luo2 lie4 ta3 li4 ya4

sentences.english: Factory buildings spread out over the hillside.
But only naming a select few neglects countless others.
sentences.chinese: 但是僅羅列了少數人就忽略了無數的其他人。

sentences.english: Peak out seven, and skyscraper highest peaks overlapping range upon range of hills, spectacular momentum.
sentences.chinese: 七峯羅列，摩天最高，層巒疊嶂，氣勢壯觀。

sentences.english: The program listed twenty-three areas where Arkansas ranked near the bottom of all states.
sentences.chinese: 片中羅列了阿肯色州在全國墊底的23個領域。

sentences.english: There is ten translations here - I am not going to read them all.
sentences.chinese: 這裏有十種解釋，我將不全部羅列。

sentences.english: Cargo manifest in accordance with Hong Kong-by-vote lists a summary of the entire vessel carrying the goods list.
sentences.chinese: 艙單是按照貨港逐票羅列全船載運貨物的彙總清單。

sentences.english: The valley is checkered with green farm fields and dotted with gray cities and towns.
sentences.chinese: 峽谷內羅列着綠色的農場，並點綴着灰色的市鎮。

sentences.english: Investors with a contrarian bent are starting to tot up reasons to consider Europe now.
sentences.chinese: 反向投資者現在開始羅列投資歐洲股市的理由。

sentences.english: What we can do is only list out these different sayings for you to just have a look.
sentences.chinese: 我們只能把這些說法羅列出來，供諸君一覽。

sentences.english: So here is my list of the top uses for baking soda.
sentences.chinese: 所以這裏我將羅列出小蘇打最常見的用法。

sentences.english: Verify addendums as noted and information addressed appropriately.
sentences.chinese: 確認補遺及信息已清晰羅列好。

sentences.english: And she began ticking them off on her fingers.
sentences.chinese: 她開始扳着手指羅列這些名字。

sentences.english: The most popular consumed seafoods were included in the Seafood Guide.
sentences.chinese: 海鮮選擇指引羅列本港最受歡迎的海鮮種類。

sentences.english: The sheer volume and variety of his accomplishments are simply astonishing.
sentences.chinese: 連爲他羅列出來的成就表都讓人震驚。

definition: to sum up/to summarize/to conclude from facts/induction (method of deduction in logic)
to relate (a story or information)/to tell or talk about/to recount/narration/telling/narrative/account
to expound (a position)/to elaborate (on a topic)/to treat (a subject)
conclusion/verdict/CL:個|个[ge4]/to conclude/to reach a verdict
